619
00:35:47,545 --> 00:35:48,679
Come in.

620
00:35:50,181 --> 00:35:51,616
Thank you.

621
00:35:56,354 --> 00:35:59,323
Principal, what is this about?

622
00:35:59,390 --> 00:36:04,328
Urumi-sensei
wanted to speak with all of you.

623
00:36:04,962 --> 00:36:06,964
So we arranged this meeting.

624
00:36:07,031 --> 00:36:08,266
A discussion…

625
00:36:09,567 --> 00:36:10,935
So, what is this about?

626
00:36:11,002 --> 00:36:11,969
MEISHIN PRIVATE ACADEMY

627
00:36:12,036 --> 00:36:13,838
It’s about Miyazawa's withdrawal.

628
00:36:14,338 --> 00:36:16,007
Could you reconsider it?

629
00:36:16,607 --> 00:36:19,210
-Sensei!
-He lied about his age and did

630
00:36:19,277 --> 00:36:21,312
compensated dating. That’s on him.

631
00:36:28,052 --> 00:36:29,353
This is a written statement.

632
00:36:29,420 --> 00:36:33,324
The woman won’t sue, and admits
he wasn’t doing compensated dating.

633
00:36:33,391 --> 00:36:35,026
She testified to it.

634
00:36:35,092 --> 00:36:38,996
TOTAL INTEGRITY

635
00:36:43,401 --> 00:36:44,335
I see.

636
00:36:46,003 --> 00:36:48,706
Then there’s no reason
to expel Miyazawa anymore.

637
00:36:52,410 --> 00:36:53,844
I see.

638
00:36:55,146 --> 00:36:57,014
But can I ask…

639
00:36:57,682 --> 00:37:00,484
what about the photo of them together?

640
00:37:02,320 --> 00:37:03,621
That is…

641
00:37:03,688 --> 00:37:06,424
Could you arrange
for me to meet this woman?

642
00:37:06,991 --> 00:37:08,292
What do you plan to do?

643
00:37:09,160 --> 00:37:11,295
I just want to hear her side of the story.

644
00:37:12,263 --> 00:37:15,766
If there was no compensated dating,

645
00:37:15,833 --> 00:37:18,936
Why did she say she’d sue?

646
00:37:19,003 --> 00:37:20,104
If you think of it,

647
00:37:20,171 --> 00:37:23,874
It just makes it look like
there was some truth to it,

648
00:37:23,941 --> 00:37:28,079
but I think you talked to her
and convinced her to settle.

649
00:37:32,650 --> 00:37:34,218
This is a school.

650
00:37:34,852 --> 00:37:36,487
We are to educate and raise students.

651
00:37:37,555 --> 00:37:39,890
The truth matters more

652
00:37:39,957 --> 00:37:42,727
than what’s written on a sheet of paper.

653
00:37:46,163 --> 00:37:48,566
What good is saving a child with a lie?

654
00:37:50,268 --> 00:37:51,502
So…

655
00:37:52,503 --> 00:37:54,338
can you let me speak to that woman?

656
00:37:55,406 --> 00:37:58,109
-But…
-I already told you that’s enough!

657
00:37:58,175 --> 00:38:01,078
-Miyazawa…
-I'm sorry.

658
00:38:02,013 --> 00:38:03,848
I’m dropping out.

659
00:38:03,914 --> 00:38:07,218
-Wait!
-Don’t make me say it again. I don’t care.

660
00:38:07,752 --> 00:38:09,420
It’s my life.

661
00:38:10,755 --> 00:38:12,890
I won’t burden anyone.

662
00:38:13,891 --> 00:38:14,759
I’m quitting school.

663
00:38:23,134 --> 00:38:24,902
Are you just trying to sound cool?

664
00:38:28,306 --> 00:38:32,443
You won't stay, and you think you'll look
good when you leave?

665
00:38:34,679 --> 00:38:37,915
Then, you're just a self-indulgent fool.

666
00:38:39,183 --> 00:38:40,451
Don't say it like that.

667
00:38:41,652 --> 00:38:44,288
I said I’m fine with it.

668
00:38:45,756 --> 00:38:47,391
Is quitting such a bad thing?

669
00:38:47,458 --> 00:38:50,961
I want to quit, but instead
I should just endure all of this?

670
00:38:51,028 --> 00:38:52,263
Isn’t that outdated?

671
00:38:52,997 --> 00:38:56,701
Well, it’s true.
These days, quitting right away

672
00:38:56,767 --> 00:38:59,303
isn’t seen as negative anymore.

673
00:39:00,104 --> 00:39:03,674
People no longer feel
they must stay in toxic environments.

674
00:39:04,275 --> 00:39:05,576
But on the flip side…

675
00:39:06,310 --> 00:39:10,481
This idea that it’s fine to quit anytime
has also become more common.

676
00:39:13,150 --> 00:39:16,721
Some do well after quitting. Others don’t.

677
00:39:17,521 --> 00:39:19,990
Why the difference?

678
00:39:21,025 --> 00:39:22,226
Do you know why?

679
00:39:25,329 --> 00:39:27,798
It’s whether you have something
you want to do or not.

680
00:39:29,600 --> 00:39:33,204
If you have a goal worth quitting for,
I won’t stop you.

681
00:39:34,138 --> 00:39:36,374
But you said you don’t care anymore.

682
00:39:37,007 --> 00:39:39,076
Quitting because you "don't care."

683
00:39:39,143 --> 00:39:42,446
You’re just acting on impulse
and not thinking ahead.

684
00:39:43,681 --> 00:39:47,218
That’s the same as a child
throwing a tantrum.

685
00:39:49,053 --> 00:39:51,622
Wherever someone like that goes,

686
00:39:52,423 --> 00:39:54,892
they’ll quit again when things get tough.

687
00:39:55,793 --> 00:39:58,262
Because there’s nothing
they really want to do.

688
00:40:00,164 --> 00:40:02,366
And if they keep quitting…

689
00:40:03,634 --> 00:40:07,204
They’ll eventually end up doing nothing,
just staying at home.

690
00:40:08,773 --> 00:40:10,708
Then they’ll start blaming themselves.

691
00:40:12,710 --> 00:40:15,246
They’ll think the world is judging them.

692
00:40:15,312 --> 00:40:17,381
They won't have a moment of peace.

693
00:40:18,282 --> 00:40:20,885
Even normal things become overwhelming.

694
00:40:21,752 --> 00:40:25,289
That mental fatigue turns into negativity,

695
00:40:25,356 --> 00:40:28,626
which creates a vicious cycle
that keeps them from moving forward.

696
00:40:32,296 --> 00:40:34,198
I’ve experienced that myself.

697
00:40:41,071 --> 00:40:43,741
Do you have something
you really want to do?

698
00:40:44,975 --> 00:40:45,910
I…

699
00:40:45,976 --> 00:40:48,979
You said you love studying
and want to go to university, right?

700
00:40:50,247 --> 00:40:52,716
Then staying in high school
is the right choice.

701
00:40:52,783 --> 00:40:55,486
If you stay here, you can chase your goal.

702
00:40:56,320 --> 00:40:59,123
So don’t say "I quit" so easily!

703
00:41:09,033 --> 00:41:11,836
I… really…

704
00:41:14,839 --> 00:41:16,040
Please!

705
00:41:17,041 --> 00:41:18,275
Let Miyazawa

706
00:41:19,043 --> 00:41:20,711
stay in school!

707
00:41:23,047 --> 00:41:23,981
I…

708
00:41:24,882 --> 00:41:25,749
don’t want to quit.

709
00:41:25,816 --> 00:41:28,152
I don’t want to leave school!

710
00:41:32,223 --> 00:41:35,860
He loves school more than anyone.
He loves studying

711
00:41:35,926 --> 00:41:37,328
and he’s a good kid.

712
00:41:38,762 --> 00:41:40,764
Are you going to take away his future?

713
00:41:43,734 --> 00:41:44,602
Moriguchi-sensei

714
00:41:45,302 --> 00:41:48,005
said schools are like companies. However…

715
00:41:48,772 --> 00:41:51,842
Private high schools
are public-interest corporations.

716
00:41:51,909 --> 00:41:54,712
Public-interest corps exist
to benefit society.

717
00:41:55,346 --> 00:41:57,014
Stop thinking about school’s profits…

718
00:41:57,081 --> 00:41:58,749
Enough is enough!

719
00:42:00,918 --> 00:42:04,221
I don’t have time to listen
to your lectures.

720
00:42:04,922 --> 00:42:06,156
No matter what’s said,

721
00:42:06,824 --> 00:42:08,626
Miyazawa is expelled.

722
00:42:15,733 --> 00:42:19,203
Quitting high school
won’t change his future that much.

723
00:42:20,638 --> 00:42:23,073
If he wants to study,
he can do it at home.

724
00:42:23,707 --> 00:42:26,110
He can take
university entrance exams, too.

725
00:42:26,176 --> 00:42:30,481
Even if he’s poor, there are ways
to get into university.

726
00:42:34,985 --> 00:42:38,589
What happens to you from here
is up to you. However,

727
00:42:39,156 --> 00:42:41,258
when someone does wrong,
they must be punished.

728
00:42:42,693 --> 00:42:44,728
It’s our job as teachers
to teach them that.

729
00:42:46,664 --> 00:42:49,433
Otherwise, children won’t grow up.

730
00:42:52,036 --> 00:42:55,172
Isn't that right, Vice-Principal?

731
00:42:59,843 --> 00:43:01,512
You’re absolutely right.

732
00:43:02,279 --> 00:43:03,681
Principal…

733
00:43:04,782 --> 00:43:05,616
do you agree?

734
00:43:26,837 --> 00:43:27,838
Today…

735
00:43:29,406 --> 00:43:32,443
I must inform you all about something.

736
00:43:35,346 --> 00:43:37,281
Keita Miyazawa…

737
00:43:40,150 --> 00:43:42,086
will be leaving school.

738
00:43:45,422 --> 00:43:47,458
What? He's quitting?

739
00:43:47,524 --> 00:43:49,526
Why?

740
00:43:50,094 --> 00:43:50,961
Why so suddenly?

741
00:43:52,730 --> 00:43:54,898
What’s going on, Keita?

742
00:43:57,234 --> 00:44:00,304
Well… a lot happened.

743
00:44:03,974 --> 00:44:05,209
I'm quitting school.

744
00:44:05,776 --> 00:44:07,678
Why? What’s the reason?

745
00:44:09,179 --> 00:44:10,247
‪So…‬

746
00:44:11,548 --> 00:44:12,549
a lot of stuff happened.

747
00:44:12,616 --> 00:44:14,585
Sensei, what's going on?

748
00:44:19,823 --> 00:44:20,758
Sensei…

749
00:44:28,899 --> 00:44:30,067
I’m sorry…

